---
description: graphify — query-first, graph refresh, freshness gate (canonical; do not use graphify cursor install)
alwaysApply: true
---

Local graph: `graphify-out/` (gitignored). Install: `py -3.12 -m pip install graphifyy`.

Do not read `.cursor/_archive/` unless the user asks to restore. Do not run `graphify cursor install` (writes `graphify.mdc` and duplicates this rule).

## Query-first (Otto — read-only)

When `graphify-out/graph.json` exists, before broad grep or file spelunking:

```bash
py -3.12 -m graphify query "<narrow question>"
py -3.12 -m graphify path "<A>" "<B>"
py -3.12 -m graphify explain "<concept>"
```

- Never load `graph.json` into context.
- Use `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` if it exists.
- `GRAPH_REPORT.md`: Corpus/Summary, Graph Freshness, God Nodes, Surprising, Suggested Questions only — skip Community Hubs and Communities.
- May run `python3 scripts/check_graphify_freshness.py` (no `--strict`). Never run `graphify update`.

## Graph refresh (user + Cline)

After lesson `code/`, `docs/`, `outputs/`, or `site/` edits:

```bash
py -3.12 -m graphify update .
```

Skip when only README, ROADMAP, glossary, or `phases/**/quiz.json` changed. Do not run `graphify site`.

## Freshness gate (Cline)

After graph refresh: `python3 scripts/check_graphify_freshness.py --strict` must exit 0.

## Do not

Commit `graphify-out/`, add CI/hooks for graphify, or create a second graphify rule file.
